<tr height="74">
<td width="226" class="s58 b11">Bangladesh/Cambodia/Lesotho to Canada (CA-LDC)</td>
<td width="5" class="s28 b5">&nbsp;</td>
<td colspan="3" class="s53 b10"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><u><b>Form B255</b></u></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;">&nbsp;(must state fabric & yarn origin)                                                            For infant/toddler & set item,  must show split HTS code (dual HTS).&nbsp;</font></td>
<td width="466" class="s62 b10">For infant/toddler & set item,  must show split HTS code (dual HTS).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
<td width="6" class="s60 b10">&nbsp;</td>
<td colspan="9" class="s63 b11">For ineligible styles:  Vendor Explanation letter required and must state fabric/yarn origins clearly.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr height="158">
<td width="226" class="s58 b4">To EU (EU-GSP) & (EU-EUR1)</td>
<td width="5" class="s28 b9">&nbsp;</td>
<td colspan="3" class="s53 b9"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><u><b>GSP Form A  or  EUR1&nbsp;</b></u></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;">When to apply GSP Form A or EUR1, refer to "Regional Gap EU Style List".                                                                                      For infant/toddler & set item, must show split HTS code (dual HTS).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><u><b>For Cambodia, India, Sri Lanka, Pakistan & Bangadesh COO</b></u></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;">&nbsp;- Form A can be replaced by Exporter's Declaration if the invoice value is &lt;/=USD8500, exporter's declaration need to be stated on&nbsp;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><b>Commercial Invoice or</b></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;">&nbsp;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><b>Packing List</b></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;">&nbsp;and must be in Exporter's letter head (see exporter declartation sample under "other requirement")&nbsp;</font></td>
<td width="88" class="s64 b9">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="466" class="s62 b9">For infant/toddler & set item, both the C/O & Comm Inv must show split HTS code (dual HTS).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
<td width="6" class="s60 b9">&nbsp;</td>
<td colspan="9" class="s28 b4"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;">Statement: "The exporter of the products covered by this document (indicate name of exporter) declares that, except where otherwise clearly indicated, these products are of (State Preferential Country of Origin) preferential origin according to rules of origin on the Generalized System of Preferences of the European Community and (</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><i>EU Cumulation&nbsp;</i></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><u><i>or</i></u></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;">&nbsp;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><i>Regional Cumulation&nbsp;</i></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><u><i>or&nbsp;</i></u></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;"><i>leave blank if from LDC country or eligible via vertcal production)</i></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:15px;">." *Note - Whether EU Cumulation or Regional Cumulation is required to be stated depends on eligiblity status on monthly style list under "Cumulation".</font></td>
</tr>
